come of the PLHIV terminating the ongoing treatment. 2.6.3 The members of the current group reported that they did not face any discrimination at the SACP. 2 7 Field Findings 2.7.1 The majority of the group was aware of the source", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e9491237-bc35-46c3-bc9a-2e833562f149": {"__data__": {"id_": "e9491237-bc35-46c3-bc9a-2e833562f149", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-services-key-populations-pakistan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Scan of Law and Policies Affecting Human Rights, Discrimination and Access to HIV and Health Services by Key Populations in Pakistan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-services-key-populations-pakistan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "95e68ca2e2255724f3fa5ab10b79383ff9e64bcaa9be000d53db9ecf1184bcb2"}, "3": {"node_id": "c5429d95-6e19-464f-923f-290539e750a5", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-services-key-populations-pakistan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "a14e64273ed3c36905e3c769e8e43842788b62c71bce6223ce8c2d6eb7d8becd"}}, "hash": "599bb2fffc48c