 system and destroying their function, resulting in the progressive depletion of the immune system; (j) \u201cHIV-positive\u201d means the presence of HIV infection as documented by the presence of HIV or HIV antibodies in the sample being tested; (k) \u201cHIV screening\u201d means a systematic application of a medical procedure or the conducting of surveys and or interviews by addressing questions to a pre-identified population, with the intent to determine the presence or absence of HIV or HIV virus and antibodies, on the basis 182 Annex 1 SINDH HIV/AIDS CONTROL TREATMENT AND PROTECTION ORDINANCE, 2013 of the results and or the response to such surveys and or interviews to a defined population, for a broad public health purpose; (l) \u201cHIV test\u201d means a medical procedure used to determine the presence or absence of HIV or HIV antibodies in", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bbce6d50-e0f5-47bb-a49b-4f1211f7df09": {"__data__": {"id_": "bbce6d50-e0f5-47bb-a49b-4f1211f7df09", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-services-key-populations-pakistan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Scan of Law and Policies Affecting Human Rights, Discrimination and Access to HIV and Health Services by Key Populations in Pakistan", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-services-key-populations-pakistan", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher"