ers as may be prescribed. (10) No act or proceedings of the Commission shall be invalid on the ground of the existence of any vacancy in the Commission. 5. (1) The Commission shall be located within the Health Department, Government of Sindh. (2) The Chairperson of the Commission and the Secretary of the Commission shall be elected by the Governing Body. (3) The Commission shall meet as often as considered necessary by the Chairperson but no less than every six months at such time and place as may be intimated by its Secretary. (4) The majority of the members of the Commission shall constitute a quorum for a meeting. Administration of Sindh AIDS Commission. 186 Annex 1 SINDH HIV/AIDS CONTROL TREATMENT AND PROTECTION ORDINANCE, 2013 (5) The decision of the Commission shall be taken by the majority of its members present and, in case of a tie, the member presiding a meeting shall have a casting vote. (6) All orders, determination and decisions of the Commission shall be taken in writing by the Secretary of the Commission. (7) The Commission shall establish a fund in such name as the Commission may determine which shall vest in the Commission and to which shall be credited \u2013 (a) grants made by the Government and the Federal Government and Local Bodies; (b) (b) income from investments made by the Commission; (c) (c) donations and endowments; (d) (d) revolving funds placed by the Government at the disposal of the Commission; and (e) (e) all other sums received by the Commission and incomes from other sources. 6.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "31c068ac-a8b6-4f22-a31c-8a4114212c8f": {"__data__": {"id_": "31c068ac-a8b6-4f22-a31c-8a4114212c8f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/scan-law-and-policies-affecting-human-rights-discrimination-and-access-hiv-and-health-