xpLOring mALe-tO-mALe Sex, gender identity And hiv trAnSmiSSiOn riSk in Fiji Ben Bavinton Niraj Singh Dipesh Shrinil Naiker Marcus Navin Deo Metuisela Talala Moji Brown Rishi Raj Singh Sanjay Dewan Simione Navokavokadrau AcknOwLedgmentS This project would not have been possible or successful without the help and support from many key people and organisations. First and foremost, we would like to thank the community members who willingly gave their time to share their personal details with us. They did this without payment and with a great amount of trust. A community-based project such as this could never have happened without such strong support and enthusiasm for the project from men who have sex with men, gays, bisexuals and transgender people in and around Suva, Nadi and Lautoka. We especially thank the community contributors who were involved in the initial development of the project: Jone Volau, Maurice Kingdon, Nicholas Mitchell, Noa Targuci (Jnr) and Sakiusa Taleaua. We\u2019d like to extend our gratitude to Jane Keith-Reid, director of the AIDS Task Force of Fiji, whose vision, unwavering support, mentoring and belief in us made this community-owned and -driven research project possible. To Ferdinand Strobel and Garry Wiseman of the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) and Edmund Settle of the UNDP Asia-Pacific Regional Centre in Bangkok, we thank you for providing the initial funds, funding the consultant\u2019s visits to Fiji, and generally supporting the project. We would like to thank Stephen Scott, formerly the International Projects officer at ACON (the AIDS Council of New South Wales, Australia), who assisted this project at its hour of need and enabled the partnership to form between ACON and the AIDS Task Force of Fiji. To ACON more generally, we are grateful for this partnership and the support provided. To Dr. Josaia Samuela, Ministry of Health, Suva, Fiji, we are grateful for your support. Our special thanks to Marlene Dutta, our external Financial Consultant, for providing administrative support for the project. Finally, to the members of the HIV Epidemiology and Prevention Program at the Kirby Institute for Infection and Immunity in Society (formerly the National Centre in HIV Epidemiology and Clinical Research) at the University of New South Wales, many thanks for your words of advice and encouragement. cOntentS GlOSSARy OF TERMS AND ACRONyMS 6 ExECuTIVE SuMMARy 7 1. INTRODuCTION 10 BACkgROUND 10 2.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "5a4a7af2-d8e3-4de1-940d-aeca78b8496a": {"__data__": {"id_": "5a4a7af2-d8e3-4de1-940d-aeca78b8496a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/secret-lives-other-voices-community-based-study-exploring-male-male-sex-gender-identity-and-hiv-transmission-risk-fiji", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Secret Lives, Other Voices...: A community-based study exploring male-to-male sex, gender identity and HIV transmission risk in Fiji", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/secret-lives-other-voices-community-based-study-exploring-male-male-sex-gender-identity-and-hiv-transmission-risk-fiji", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "5400b21647002f14391a7bdaf7428d9f00186a46a9a232b417c2ff67ff66ec2b"}, "2": {"node_id": "013b065b-339b-432a-b808-e0822b9ad9ef", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/secret-lives-other-voices-community-based-study-exploring-male-male-sex-gender-identity-and-hiv-transmi