ce at national, regional, and international forums lobbying for appropriate representation and meaningful engagement of marginalised communities in especially responding to emerging issues around HIV/STIs and sexual health.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "16476f65-ebea-4159-814b-21d6cb4ec279": {"__data__": {"id_": "16476f65-ebea-4159-814b-21d6cb4ec279", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-technical-consultation", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Socio-economic impact of HIV at the household levels in Asia and the Pacific - Report on Technical Consultation", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-technical-consultation", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "6098fd9d2f954d48657680f605d270411c80d22b2f03416c392a7cf424993426"}, "3": {"node_id": "ec4ae285-0d2c-4cf8-97a9-a88f55d4b692", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-technical-consultation", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "260eacbd6b0b6dc3bd87b503257bbe019ac13ace697cce82dcf57df9f79a79fa"}}, "hash": "f932810ba33ede31d686518a01b48e21635189207664beb94d2213b6fa7fe7fb", "text": "Report on Technical Consultation Socio-economic impact of HIV at the household levels in Asia and the Pacific 3-4 March 2009 Colombo UNDP Regional Centre for Asia Pacific, Colombo Published in August 2009 Copyright \u00a9 UNDP Regional Centre in Colombo Regional HIV & Development Programme for Asia & the Pacific UNDP Regional Centre in Colombo 23, Independence Avenue, Colombo 7, Sri Lanka. Tel: +94 11 4526400 Fax: +94 11 4526410 rcc@undp.org www.undprcc.lk All rights reserved ISBN 978-955-1031-20-6 Prepared by a team comprising Caitlin Wiesen, G. Pramod Kumar, Ramamani Sundar and Tiruni Yasaratne Layout and design by A&D Advertising The views expressed in this publication are those of the authors and do not necessarily represent those of the United Nations, including UNDP, or their Member States. The text and data in this publication may be reproduced as long as the source is cited. Contents Overview 01 DAY 1 02 OVERVIEW OF STUDY METHODOLOGIES & LEARNING: INDIA & CHINA EMERGING ISSUES AND THEIR SOCIO-ECONOMIC IMPACT Socio-economic impact of HIV and AIDS on households in India 05 A study in six high prevalence states: learning and experience Socio-economic impact of HIV at the household levels in China 11 A five province study: learning and experience Socio-economic impact of HIV in Indonesia 17 A seven province study: update on the methodology and the process Socio-economic impact of HIV and AIDS on households in Vietnam: 21 The impact on poverty Socio-economic impact of HIV on households in Cambodia 25 A national study: the methodology and process HIV and food security in Asia - preliminary findings from the 31 existing studies and implications for future studies Global financial crisis: implications for Asia 35 Spousal transmission of HIV 39 An example focused on intimate partner violence and HIV infection: findings from a national sample of Indian husband-wife Dyads DAY 2 44 MODEL QUESTIONNAIRE: BRAINSTORMING AND ANALYSES NEXT STEPS I. Brainstorming on the questionnaire 45 II. Common framework for reports 48 Annexure 1: Agenda 53 Annexure 2: List of participants 56 Overview A notable weakness of the responses to HIV in the Asia Pacific region is the inadequate acknowledgement of the impact of the epidemic on people and communities, and the absence of appropriate steps for impact mitigation. People living with HIV and their households, including those who suffered AIDS-deaths, are acutely burdened by Illnesses, loss of jobs and income, rising medical expenses, depletion of savings and other resources, discrimination, social exclusion and psychological stress related morbidity. The impact is also felt on the status of women as well as education of children. Based on its mandate1 to lead the human development dimensions of the epidemic, including its social and economic implications, UNDP Regional HIV and Development Programme has taken steps to study the impact of the epidemic2 at the household level in select countries of the Asia Pacific region and to recommend impact mitigation steps. It developed a methodology based on a large-scale study in India3 and helped UNDP COs in China, Cambodia and Indo- nesia launch studies on the impact. Vietnam launched a similar study incorporating relevant elements from the methodology. They are under various stages of implementation. To share the learning from the studies as well as the progress and challenges; and to discuss how best to incorporate critical emerging issues including spousal transmission, the impact of volatile food and fuel prices and the current financial crisis in the studies; and appropriately revise the methodology and questionnaire, the Regional HIV Programme organized a two- day technical consultation in Colombo from 3-4 March 2009. The consultation was attended by research teams and UNDP staff from Cambodia, China, India, Indonesia and Vietnam, and leading experts on the socio-economic analysis of HIV, and the members of the Regional HIV Programme. This report presents the summary of the technical presentations and discussions at the consultation as well as the outputs such as the survey questionnaire. The report has been prepared with a view to guide research and analytical efforts for studying the various dimen- sions of the socio-economic impact of HIV on people living with HIV and their households. To enhance the utility of the report, the presentations have been featured as technical papers and the discussions thereof have been summarized with considerable attention to operational details. The concept note, agenda and reference materials are presented in the annexure and a companion CD-ROM.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ec4ae285-0d2c-4cf8-97a9-a88f55d4b692": {"__data__": {"id_": "ec4ae285-0d2c-4cf8-97a9-a88f55d4b692", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-technical-consultation", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Socio-economic impact of HIV at the household levels in Asia and the Pacific - Report on Technical Consultation", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-technical-consultation", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "6098fd9d2f954d48657680f605d270411c80d22b2f03416c392a7cf424993426"}, "2": {"node_id": "16476f65-ebea-4159-814b-21d6cb4ec279", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-levels-asia-and-pacific-report-t